						<div>Dear IV sangha,<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />Happy New Year!  This evening we will have our first Ocean Mist Sangha zazen sitting for 2015.  <br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /><b>This evening will be a Full Moon Ceremony</b>.
 <br clear="none" />Due a work commitment for me, Brianna Morseth will lead the session.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />Our 
precept this evening is the first grave precept: 'Do not Kill' <i>or</i>  'Non-<span>Killing</span> (Giving Life)':<br clear="none" />
							<div>
<br clear="none" /></div>
							<div style="margin-left:40px"><i>'I will recognize that I am <span>not</span> separate from all that
 is.  This is the practice of Non-<span>Killing</span>. I will <span>not</span> lead a harmful 
life, nor encourage others to <span>do</span> so. I will live in harmony with all 
life and the environment that sustains it.</i>'<br clear="none" />
</div>
							<div style="margin-left:40px"><br clear="none" /></div>
							<div style="margin-left:40px">Our sangha holds a Full Moon Ceremony every four weeks around the time of 
the full moon, and use it as an opportunity to reflect on the 3 Refuges,
 the 3 Tenets and 10 Grave Precepts.  At each ceremony we meditate 
on, and later discuss, one practice or precept in particular. <br clear="none" /></div><font face="arial"><br clear="none" />Please forward this invitation widely - all are welcome!<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /></font>
						</div><font face="arial">Our updated 2015 schedule is on our website at: <a shape="rect" href="http://oceanmistsangha.wordpress.com/sitting-schedule-2014/">http://oceanmistsangha.wordpress.com/sitting-schedule-2014/</a><br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /></font>
					</div><font face="arial">The Morning Mist sangha continues to sit at 7am each weekday at the Chapel.<br clear="none" /></font>
					<div><font face="arial"><a shape="rect" href="http://oceanmistsangha.wordpress.com/sitting-schedule-2014/"></a></font>
